article.headline: San Diego 64, Oregon 57
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Gyno Pomare had 16 points and 8 rebounds to lead San Diego to a 64-57 victory over Oregon at the Rose Garden Arena on Saturday. Chris Lewis had 15 points and Rob Jones added 14 and six rebounds for the Toreros (5-6), who snapped a three-game losing streak. Tajuan Porter had 18 points for Oregon (4-5). LeKendric Longmire added 12. Oregon trailed by as many as 15 points in the second half, but briefly threatened when Churchill Odia's 3-pointer with 38.4 seconds left narrowed the gap to 59-53. It was as close as he Ducks could come.
